message.content:
This command connects to an EC2 instance on Amazon Web Services (AWS) using the Secure Shell (SSH) protocol and a specified private key file (~/UserKey.pem). It also sets up a local forwarding of port 5900 to the specified destination IP address and port number (ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com:25900). The -C option enables compression, which can improve the performance of the connection over slow or unreliable networks.

In simple terms, this command allows you to remotely access a server running on an EC2 instance with the specified credentials and set up a forwarding of a local port to connect to another service (likely a VNC server) running on the remote server.
